To transform a PRD into the standard format:
1. Identify the product name and version from the input PRD.
2. Extract the product overview, typically found in the introduction or summary section.
3. Extract the objectives or goals of the product.
4. Identify the key features, often listed in a "Features" or "Functionality" section.
5. Look for user stories, if present, usually in a "User Stories" or "Use Cases" section.
6. Extract any non-functional requirements, such as performance or security needs.
7. Use the extracted information to fill in the standard PRD template located at `prd-template.md`.
